doc.after: Stromatolites are layered accretionary structures formed in shallow water by the trapping binding and cementation of sedimentary grains by biofilms of microorganisms especially cyanobacteria 27 Stromatolites provide some of the most ancient fossil records of life on Earth dating back more than 3 5 billion years ago 28
